SELECTOR                - MATCH

*                       - any element
body                    - applies to the whole document
h1, h2, h3              - applies to selected matched html tags 
.poem                   - html elements with class=.poem
div.warning             - div whose list-attribute class includes warning ex <div class="toto" class="warning"></div>
                        !!! Equivalent to div[class~=warning], see below
#hidden                 - single element whose id=hidden
a                       - links of any kinds
a:link                  - links which have not yet been clicked on or visited 
a:visited               - links whose targets have already been visited 
a:active                - links which have just be clicked and page is loading ... 
a:hover                 - links under the mouse
input:focus             - input element which has focus
a[target]               - links with attribute 'target'  (iframe) ... 
a[target="iframe2"]     - links whose attribute  target is = iframe2 ... 
a[class~="warning"]     - links whose list-attribute class includes 'warning' as an element. Same as a.warning!
                        !!! Note that an element can have several classes
a#ID                    - single link whose (non-attribute) id=ID 
a > img                 - images (not link!) which are direct children of links
a img                   - images (not links) which are direct or indirect children of a link
div > p:first-child     - any P element that is the first child of a DIV element
p:first-child em        - any em element that is some descendant of a P element that is a first child
.post + .post           - matches any element .post element immediately preceded by a sibling element .post
.post1 + .post2         - matches any element .post2 element immediately preceded by a sibling element .post1

more at http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS2/selector.html

#----------------------------------------------------------------------
# FORM SUFFIXES

input:required
input:optional
input:valid
input:invalid
input:default
input:in-range
input:out-of-range
input:not()

#----------------------------------------------------------------------
# FORM ATTRIBUTES SELECTORS

[autofocus]
[autocomplete]
[list]
[placeholder]
[type=range]
[multiple]

#----------------------------------------------------------------------
# SELECTORS with positioning

.table1 tbody span.check::before{                   # <-- insert the image before the <span class="check"> element
    content : url(../images/check0.png)
}

